		<DisplayName>Yqaesi the Gamekeeper</DisplayName>
		<Backstory>Given their great passion for hunting, larger Drota settlements tend to quickly depopulate any quarry from the surrounding lands.  As such, they have recently begun captive breeding programs to ensure that prey exists to be hunted when desired, at least for those of means.  Yqaesi was one of the first such Gamekeepers, and is quite adept at managing the incessant demands to release 'just one more' against the needs of maintaining a viable supply of captive stock, and applying the appropriate political pressure to ensure that no one faction hoards the game supply to themselves.  Nonetheless, she managed to annoy the wrong party at the wrong time by refusing to supply a captive Gnomish youth for a 'blooding' ceremony for a powerful Drota commander's favored offspring.  Sensing that her own well-being was in danger, she set loose the entire captive stock as a diversion and made her escape.  She now seeks to apply her skills at 'grooming the stock' elsewhere.</Backstory>

